1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:02:00,000
(Watch on www.kissasia.club Support Admin)

2
00:02:56,021 --> 00:02:57,272
Not disappointed.

3
00:02:58,606 --> 00:02:59,774
Surprised

4
00:03:00,442 --> 00:03:03,737
it seems like Supremo has
a soft spot for you.

5
00:03:04,325 --> 00:03:07,657
I don't need that or want his help.

6
00:03:09,617 --> 00:03:11,369
Do you have a family?

7
00:03:11,995 --> 00:03:12,995
Ms. Shion?

8
00:03:15,832 --> 00:03:17,667
Why are you suddenly
engaging in small talk?

9
00:03:19,002 --> 00:03:20,336
My older sister Allison.

10
00:03:22,881 --> 00:03:24,340
Textbook eldest daughter

11
00:03:26,426 --> 00:03:28,386
she's good at everything, she's beautiful

12
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,232
and brave.

13
00:03:30,722 --> 00:03:31,779
I'm done.

14
00:03:32,807 --> 00:03:34,017
A bit slower than I thought.

15
00:03:39,647 --> 00:03:40,647
But

16
00:03:41,357 --> 00:03:42,427
you're good to go.

17
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:53,703
Who's more handsome

18
00:03:54,245 --> 00:03:55,413
me or that Supremo?

19
00:03:57,290 --> 00:03:58,583
Of course, you!

20
00:03:59,084 --> 00:04:00,627
You have time for your friend

21
00:04:02,378 --> 00:04:03,755
but when I call upon you

22
00:04:05,924 --> 00:04:07,509
it's not right to keep me waiting.

23
00:04:09,398 --> 00:04:10,236
Okay.

24
00:04:10,261 --> 00:04:11,268
Fine.

25
00:04:11,513 --> 00:04:13,223
If that's all, goodbye...

26
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:15,393
Supremo.

27
00:04:18,728 --> 00:04:20,105
You remind me of someone.

28
00:04:22,816 --> 00:04:23,854
Madam?

29
00:04:26,945 --> 00:04:28,570
You're going to regret this.

30
00:04:28,571 --> 00:04:30,073
Raze will know about this.

31
00:04:30,115 --> 00:04:31,115
Is it true?

32
00:04:31,699 --> 00:04:33,201
You started a fight with Roxane?

33
00:04:33,326 --> 00:04:34,494
Aren't you scared?

34
00:04:35,745 --> 00:04:37,664
You’re putting yourself in danger.

35
00:04:37,914 --> 00:04:40,458
What do you think the boss will do to her?

36
00:04:41,251 --> 00:04:42,395
Death.

37
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:44,587
I'm sure he'll kill her.

38
00:04:44,629 --> 00:04:46,381
You're not Raze Silvenia.

39
00:04:47,144 --> 00:04:48,228
Shut your mouth!

40
00:04:49,201 --> 00:04:52,496
Your secret is my secret.

41
00:05:16,286 --> 00:05:17,303
Hey!

42
00:05:17,328 --> 00:05:18,822
Where do you think you're going?

43
00:05:19,497 --> 00:05:20,874
Let go!

44
00:07:18,783 --> 00:07:20,285
Thank God, you're safe!

45
00:07:21,393 --> 00:07:23,712
Are you always going to make
us worry about you?

46
00:07:24,196 --> 00:07:25,947
I thought we're all
in this together?

47
00:07:26,615 --> 00:07:28,574
Why are you always going
about it on your own?

48
00:07:28,575 --> 00:07:30,535
What's important is
she's here now.

49
00:07:31,002 --> 00:07:32,211
He's right, Van.

50
00:07:33,135 --> 00:07:34,135
No.

51
00:07:34,299 --> 00:07:37,051
Van's right. It's my fault.

52
00:07:39,049 --> 00:07:40,718
I was being selfish.

53
00:07:41,027 --> 00:07:43,363
I didn't think about
how you would feel.

54
00:07:43,761 --> 00:07:45,388
I'm really sorry, guys.

55
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:00,938
Thank you guys.

56
00:08:01,488 --> 00:08:04,283
I'm grateful because you’re here.

57
00:08:05,909 --> 00:08:08,314
Even if this place is a hellhole.

58
00:08:08,372 --> 00:08:09,665
We’re friends

59
00:08:09,981 --> 00:08:11,191
we're going to stick together

60
00:08:11,957 --> 00:08:14,168
no matter what hell
we end up in.

61
00:08:16,135 --> 00:08:17,135
Wait

62
00:08:17,303 --> 00:08:19,096
was Dave with you?

63
00:08:20,025 --> 00:08:21,025
What?

64
00:08:21,307 --> 00:08:22,307
He wasn't.

65
00:08:23,142 --> 00:08:24,142
Huh?

66
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:25,311
Then where is he?

67
00:08:26,229 --> 00:08:27,897
He hasn't come back
from his classes.

68
00:08:28,105 --> 00:08:29,482
Let's look for him!

69
00:08:29,941 --> 00:08:30,566
Huh?

70
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:32,360
Bloody Night has already started.

71
00:08:32,524 --> 00:08:34,214
How could we find him?

72
00:08:34,583 --> 00:08:36,917
Zein, your recklessness
rubbed off on him.

73
00:08:37,406 --> 00:08:38,824
Are you really blaming
me for this?

74
00:08:39,158 --> 00:08:41,535
I'm joking, you're being too serious.

75
00:08:43,454 --> 00:08:45,163
But where is he?

76
00:08:45,164 --> 00:08:47,165
He knows best that
people in this place

77
00:08:47,166 --> 00:08:48,784
turn to savages at this time.

78
00:08:48,809 --> 00:08:50,895
Guys, please. Let's find him!

79
00:08:51,378 --> 00:08:52,797
No one gets left behind, right?

80
00:08:53,464 --> 00:08:54,298
Mia's right.

81
00:08:54,299 --> 00:08:56,299
Dave can't survive alone outside.

82
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,592
It’s too dangerous.

83
00:08:57,593 --> 00:08:58,844
This will be dangerous

84
00:08:59,428 --> 00:09:00,428
but I'm in.

85
00:09:01,055 --> 00:09:02,305
Matt and I will find him.

86
00:09:02,306 --> 00:09:03,391
Hold on, wait!

87
00:09:03,683 --> 00:09:05,141
Aren't you the ones who said

88
00:09:05,142 --> 00:09:06,435
that it's dangerous outside

89
00:09:06,602 --> 00:09:07,728
when it's Bloody Night?

90
00:09:07,979 --> 00:09:09,188
Now, you're going outside?

91
00:09:10,523 --> 00:09:11,883
If anything happens to both of you

92
00:09:12,191 --> 00:09:13,401
it'll be harder for everyone.

93
00:09:13,734 --> 00:09:14,902
Zein is right.

94
00:09:15,444 --> 00:09:18,864
It'll be worse if the two of
you disappear too.

95
00:09:19,532 --> 00:09:21,324
Let's just wait for him here.

96
00:09:21,325 --> 00:09:22,535
He'll return to us.

97
00:09:22,785 --> 00:09:23,785
Okay?

98
00:09:23,911 --> 00:09:25,413
Let's just guard the doors.

99
00:09:25,746 --> 00:09:27,748
So we can open the
doors immediately

100
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:30,542
once he returns.

101
00:09:30,543 --> 00:09:31,543
Okay?

102
00:09:35,089 --> 00:09:36,089
Mia.

103
00:09:48,436 --> 00:09:50,438
Where did Dave go?

104
00:09:51,314 --> 00:09:54,233
Is waiting for him
the right decision?

105
00:09:54,567 --> 00:09:55,860
Is he still alive?

106
00:09:56,694 --> 00:09:59,405
What if he came across
the Black Blood Gang?

107
00:10:03,492 --> 00:10:05,077
Now I know how my friends feel

108
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:08,164
when I leave without
telling them.

109
00:10:45,583 --> 00:10:47,093
In this place

110
00:10:47,119 --> 00:10:50,330
the nights are longer
than daylight.

111
00:10:50,331 --> 00:10:52,683
If you want to live

112
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:59,298
you have to endure all the
screaming until morning.

113
00:11:37,211 --> 00:11:38,211
Dave...

114
00:11:44,051 --> 00:11:46,595
Dave, where have you been?

115
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:52,767
Ouch.

116
00:11:52,935 --> 00:11:53,935
It hurts.

117
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:58,300
What happened?

118
00:11:58,325 --> 00:11:59,325
Where have you been?

119
00:11:59,692 --> 00:12:03,363
I was hiding outside until
the noises stopped.

120
00:12:03,696 --> 00:12:04,530
Dave? Dave!

121
00:12:04,613 --> 00:12:05,131
Hey!

122
00:12:05,156 --> 00:12:06,156
Dave!

123
00:12:06,615 --> 00:12:07,657
We were worried sick about you.

124
00:12:07,658 --> 00:12:08,778
Water... I'll get him water.

125
00:12:08,803 --> 00:12:10,430
Here, drink some water.

126
00:12:11,412 --> 00:12:12,412
What was out there?

127
00:12:12,496 --> 00:12:13,745
What happened to you, bro?

128
00:12:14,290 --> 00:12:15,374
What happened to you, bro?

129
00:12:15,541 --> 00:12:17,626
Why did you return so late?

130
00:12:17,956 --> 00:12:19,750
Didn't you notice the time?

131
00:12:19,966 --> 00:12:21,718
I needed fresh air after class.

132
00:12:22,047 --> 00:12:23,757
On the verge of Bloody Night?

133
00:12:24,133 --> 00:12:25,384
You needed to get some air?

134
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,052
Why?

135
00:12:27,053 --> 00:12:28,773
I'm sorry, guys. I didn't
want you to worry.

136
00:12:29,555 --> 00:12:30,973
I should get some sleep.

137
00:12:32,725 --> 00:12:33,725
Dave!

138
00:12:34,477 --> 00:12:37,146
But seriously, he needed
to get some air?

139
00:12:37,771 --> 00:12:38,939
He should've known better.

140
00:12:39,023 --> 00:12:40,024
Exactly.

141
00:12:40,566 --> 00:12:42,401
You should've known
better too, Zein.

142
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:43,944
Now you know how it feels like

143
00:12:43,945 --> 00:12:46,025
when one of your friends
leaves during Bloody Night.

144
00:12:47,114 --> 00:12:48,324
It's not funny, right?

145
00:12:48,616 --> 00:12:49,742
Excuse me.

146
00:12:50,701 --> 00:12:51,911
Guys, guys...

147
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:53,245
you know

148
00:12:53,246 --> 00:12:54,330
you need to chill.

149
00:12:54,538 --> 00:12:55,538
Calm down.

150
00:12:55,581 --> 00:12:57,165
Let's just sleep it off.

151
00:12:57,166 --> 00:12:59,417
You're right, let's just
sleep it off.

152
00:12:59,418 --> 00:13:00,211
Dave!

153
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:01,295
Dave!

154
00:13:14,058 --> 00:13:15,017
Oh my god! Oh my god!

155
00:13:15,018 --> 00:13:16,602
We're going to be late!

156
00:13:17,102 --> 00:13:19,079
Is Sir Alvarez' class your first class?

157
00:13:19,104 --> 00:13:20,647
Exactly. What are we going to do?

158
00:13:20,648 --> 00:13:21,857
We're already late.

159
00:13:22,829 --> 00:13:24,413
Stop overreacting.

160
00:13:24,508 --> 00:13:26,635
We can skip the class

161
00:13:26,862 --> 00:13:29,281
cause it'll be done in thirty minutes.

162
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,294
Didn't you know that it's our
periodical exam today, Zein?

163
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:33,661
Is it really?

164
00:13:33,661 --> 00:13:34,661
Oh my god

165
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:35,993
I wasn't informed.

166
00:13:36,539 --> 00:13:38,790
You shouldn't be nonchalant, Zein.

167
00:13:38,791 --> 00:13:40,334
What if we fail class?

168
00:13:41,919 --> 00:13:43,254
Morning!

169
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:46,381
You know since we're late

170
00:13:46,468 --> 00:13:47,719
let's have some food.

171
00:13:48,425 --> 00:13:49,134
F.T, bro.

172
00:13:49,135 --> 00:13:50,386
F.T!

173
00:13:51,428 --> 00:13:52,137
Hey

174
00:13:52,138 --> 00:13:53,722
isn't anyone concerned

175
00:13:54,139 --> 00:13:56,349
that periodical tests are
16% of our grade.

176
00:13:56,350 --> 00:13:58,184
We'll definitely fail.

177
00:13:58,185 --> 00:14:01,313
What about our dream to
get into the highest ten?

178
00:14:01,514 --> 00:14:02,598
I almost forgot.

179
00:14:03,065 --> 00:14:05,775
That's why they're disappointed this much

180
00:14:05,776 --> 00:14:08,403
they won't be able to join the highest ten.

181
00:14:08,404 --> 00:14:11,740
They won't be able to leave this place.

182
00:14:13,810 --> 00:14:14,811
Erase. Erase.

183
00:14:14,994 --> 00:14:18,128
Hightest ten or not, we'll
get out of this place.

184
00:14:19,081 --> 00:14:20,415
You know guys

185
00:14:20,416 --> 00:14:21,809
that's the hunger talking.

186
00:14:21,834 --> 00:14:22,793
Let's just eat

187
00:14:22,794 --> 00:14:24,420
so we can get calm.

188
00:14:24,469 --> 00:14:25,745
That smells good!

189
00:14:26,463 --> 00:14:29,216
Hey, is that sinigang?

190
00:14:29,717 --> 00:14:31,111
Of course it is.

191
00:14:31,136 --> 00:14:32,927
Zein's favorite.

192
00:14:32,928 --> 00:14:34,805
And everyone's favorite.

193
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:36,347
Okay, let's just eat.

194
00:14:36,348 --> 00:14:37,348
Let's go.

195
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:39,976
- You're so thoughtful.
- I'll help you, Mia.

196
00:14:39,977 --> 00:14:41,227
I'll set up the table.

197
00:14:41,228 --> 00:14:42,449
I'll help you with that.

198
00:14:48,085 --> 00:14:49,104
I'll put this right here.

199
00:14:49,129 --> 00:14:50,129
Okay.

200
00:14:50,279 --> 00:14:51,363
This is my station.

201
00:15:04,209 --> 00:15:05,711
Periodical exam?

202
00:15:05,961 --> 00:15:08,041
Does anyone pass those kinds
of exams here in Hell U?

203
00:15:08,672 --> 00:15:10,673
Isn't surviving Bloody Night
more imporant

204
00:15:10,674 --> 00:15:12,259
than any kind of exam?

205
00:15:12,426 --> 00:15:13,844
Exam your face.

206
00:15:13,969 --> 00:15:16,472
Sometimes, Jerome has a point.

207
00:15:16,764 --> 00:15:17,764
Nice one, bro.

208
00:15:18,515 --> 00:15:19,391
Whatever

209
00:15:19,475 --> 00:15:20,892
if you fail

210
00:15:20,893 --> 00:15:22,978
don't come crying to us, okay?

211
00:15:23,479 --> 00:15:24,371
Me?

212
00:15:24,396 --> 00:15:24,938
Yes, you!

213
00:15:24,938 --> 00:15:25,814
Me, crying?

214
00:15:25,814 --> 00:15:26,690
Exactly.

215
00:15:26,691 --> 00:15:28,232
That's for weaklings.

216
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,233
Like you.

217
00:15:34,323 --> 00:15:35,949
Hey, Zein. Are you okay?

218
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:37,533
Does it taste bad?

219
00:15:39,328 --> 00:15:40,954
It's delicious.

220
00:15:41,538 --> 00:15:42,623
You're a great cook.

221
00:15:42,748 --> 00:15:43,748
Hey

222
00:15:43,874 --> 00:15:45,754
they're acting like we
aren't in the room again.

223
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:50,673
I smell something fishy.

224
00:15:50,923 --> 00:15:52,299
Jerome, you know what

225
00:15:52,508 --> 00:15:53,300
that’s hunger that’s talking.

226
00:15:53,301 --> 00:15:56,261
Come on, I'll shove this
bone up your mouth.

227
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:10,441
Are you done with you assignment?

228
00:16:10,442 --> 00:16:11,193
Why?

229
00:16:11,194 --> 00:16:13,696
His subject discussions are faulty.

230
00:16:14,947 --> 00:16:15,947
Oh, fu-

231
00:16:20,119 --> 00:16:21,119
what’s that?

232
00:16:22,579 --> 00:16:23,622
It seems real

233
00:16:23,914 --> 00:16:25,165
I don't know.

234
00:16:25,874 --> 00:16:27,041
Should we be worried?

235
00:16:27,042 --> 00:16:28,042
You think?

236
00:16:28,210 --> 00:16:29,461
It's Dave's fault.

237
00:16:29,628 --> 00:16:30,462
Yeah, it’s Dave fault again.

238
00:16:30,462 --> 00:16:31,502
Why is it me all the time?

239
00:16:31,588 --> 00:16:32,564
Good morning, Sir.

240
00:16:32,589 --> 00:16:33,589
Ms. Shion.

241
00:16:36,427 --> 00:16:37,427
Guys

242
00:16:37,845 --> 00:16:38,721
I'll go ahead.

243
00:16:38,722 --> 00:16:40,054
I need to take care of something.

244
00:16:40,055 --> 00:16:41,055
I'll come with you.

245
00:16:41,473 --> 00:16:42,725
There's no need, Matt.

246
00:16:43,204 --> 00:16:45,536
You know, SSG Secretary duties.

247
00:16:45,561 --> 00:16:48,230
Trust me, I can do this.

248
00:16:48,397 --> 00:16:49,397
Bye.

249
00:16:51,483 --> 00:16:51,942
Let's go.

250
00:16:51,943 --> 00:16:53,652
Ms. Shion, why were
you absent earlier?

251
00:16:54,254 --> 00:16:56,660
Sir, can we retake the exam?

252
00:16:57,448 --> 00:16:59,199
You don't need to
retake your exams.

253
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:02,161
I'll make sure your grades
are high even without it.

254
00:17:02,185 --> 00:17:03,478
You’ll really do that, sir?

255
00:17:04,538 --> 00:17:06,247
My friends will be happy
to hear about this.

256
00:17:06,248 --> 00:17:07,499
I appreciate this, sir.

257
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:08,917
Don't thank me yet.

258
00:17:11,336 --> 00:17:12,921
How's your secretary duties?

259
00:17:13,172 --> 00:17:14,214
Hell.

260
00:17:14,798 --> 00:17:16,382
It’s so hard to relate to people

261
00:17:16,383 --> 00:17:18,010
who aren't in the same wavelength.

262
00:17:19,052 --> 00:17:21,722
But why is that your concern, sir?

263
00:17:22,431 --> 00:17:23,681
Don't worry about your grades

264
00:17:23,682 --> 00:17:24,850
I'll handle that.

265
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:27,394
But remember what you
need to do for me.

266
00:17:28,228 --> 00:17:29,271
Thank you sir

267
00:17:32,232 --> 00:17:33,816
but I don't have an idea yet

268
00:17:33,817 --> 00:17:35,694
as to where the hidden
laboratory is located.

269
00:17:35,903 --> 00:17:37,820
Even the SSG members

270
00:17:37,821 --> 00:17:39,782
haven't mentioned
anything about it.

271
00:17:40,866 --> 00:17:42,367
Are you even sure there is one?

272
00:17:44,578 --> 00:17:45,537
Naturally

273
00:17:45,538 --> 00:17:47,372
they wouldn't mention it to you.

274
00:17:48,457 --> 00:17:49,457
Trust me

275
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,585
just do your secretary duties

276
00:17:52,990 --> 00:17:55,659
monitor all their movements.

277
00:17:57,019 --> 00:17:58,896
What if they catch me, sir?

278
00:18:01,672 --> 00:18:04,174
I'm not ready to die
yet, Sir Alvarez.

279
00:18:05,554 --> 00:18:06,972
I still need to escape

280
00:18:07,893 --> 00:18:09,436
with my friends

281
00:18:09,686 --> 00:18:11,480
from this hellhole.

282
00:18:12,481 --> 00:18:14,650
Be careful, Zein

283
00:18:15,234 --> 00:18:18,278
because everyone's safety
is now in your hands.

284
00:18:22,449 --> 00:18:23,784
There's a storm coming.

285
00:18:25,244 --> 00:18:26,370
Be a demon.

286
00:18:27,287 --> 00:18:29,373
Blend in with the SSG and admin.

287
00:18:29,683 --> 00:18:33,300
But don't ever empathize with them.

288
00:18:34,336 --> 00:18:35,420
Can you do that?

289
00:19:21,462 --> 00:19:23,593
Do I need to be a demon like them

290
00:19:23,594 --> 00:19:25,603
so I could get a fair fight?

291
00:19:28,402 --> 00:19:31,072
Do I need to be more
savage than them?

292
00:19:49,494 --> 00:19:50,828
I don't want to die yet.

293
00:19:50,829 --> 00:19:51,831
Please.

294
00:19:51,856 --> 00:19:53,398
We can't do anything.

295
00:19:53,624 --> 00:19:54,583
They don't have hearts.

296
00:19:54,584 --> 00:19:56,018
You're monsters!

297
00:19:56,043 --> 00:19:57,002
You're just like them.

298
00:19:57,003 --> 00:19:58,337
You're a monster!

299
00:19:58,962 --> 00:20:01,005
We thought you'd be the next Samantha

300
00:20:01,006 --> 00:20:03,592
but just like her,
you can't fix anything.

301
00:20:08,298 --> 00:20:09,634
Samantha?

302
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,400
Number nine?

303
00:20:19,425 --> 00:20:20,676
Number nine!

304
00:20:21,158 --> 00:20:22,493
You’re a monster!

305
00:20:23,862 --> 00:20:25,739
Monsters! All of you!

306
00:20:49,629 --> 00:20:50,629
Good morning.

307
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:51,902
Madam Violet.

308
00:20:52,399 --> 00:20:53,859
Master Francisco.

309
00:20:54,087 --> 00:20:55,380
Good morning.

310
00:20:59,141 --> 00:21:04,563
Aren't you going to
greet us, Ms. Shion?

311
00:21:06,552 --> 00:21:08,846
Good morning, Master Francisco.

312
00:21:09,386 --> 00:21:10,470
Madam Violet.

313
00:21:11,828 --> 00:21:13,121
Samantha.

314
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:14,310
Madam

315
00:21:16,213 --> 00:21:17,213
let's begin.

316
00:21:29,744 --> 00:21:31,913
Good morning, our dearest students.

317
00:21:32,504 --> 00:21:34,473
We are gathered here today

318
00:21:34,474 --> 00:21:37,685
to honor our late headmaster

319
00:21:37,686 --> 00:21:39,437
Dominic Valdez.

320
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:40,863
I'm delighted

321
00:21:41,387 --> 00:21:45,266
that we are free from his foolish
leadership after all these years.

322
00:21:45,610 --> 00:21:46,944
After all these years.

323
00:21:47,194 --> 00:21:48,762
Isn't it funny?

324
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:51,851
No!

325
00:21:52,071 --> 00:21:53,489
He didn't kill himself!

326
00:21:53,605 --> 00:21:56,024
You killed headmaster Valdez!

327
00:21:56,413 --> 00:21:57,414
They killed him?

328
00:21:58,415 --> 00:22:00,709
Who said he died?

329
00:22:01,460 --> 00:22:02,461
You're right

330
00:22:03,688 --> 00:22:05,356
we killed him.

331
00:22:05,756 --> 00:22:07,674
And you'll be next.

332
00:22:08,008 --> 00:22:09,008
Just come with us.

333
00:22:09,801 --> 00:22:10,343
Let go of me!

334
00:22:10,343 --> 00:22:10,969
Where are you taking me?

335
00:22:10,969 --> 00:22:11,969
Stop resisting.

336
00:22:12,137 --> 00:22:13,512
This is absurd!

337
00:22:13,513 --> 00:22:14,056
Van!

338
00:22:14,057 --> 00:22:16,684
You killed the late headmaster

339
00:22:16,977 --> 00:22:18,311
why is he the one being punished?

340
00:22:18,937 --> 00:22:20,730
The two of you should be punished?

341
00:22:21,445 --> 00:22:23,822
Oh? You guys can laugh now!

342
00:22:24,754 --> 00:22:27,169
However you try to hide it

343
00:22:27,364 --> 00:22:31,489
the student body knows

344
00:22:31,824 --> 00:22:35,542
that you killed the headmaster!

345
00:22:39,156 --> 00:22:40,824
Get rid of her!

346
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,400
No!

347
00:22:42,459 --> 00:22:42,918
Stop!

348
00:22:42,918 --> 00:22:43,376
Let go!

349
00:22:43,377 --> 00:22:44,586
You can't do that.

350
00:22:45,796 --> 00:22:48,298
Van's protected under council rules.

351
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:51,117
You're really testing me, Ms. Shion.

352
00:22:51,442 --> 00:22:52,551
Get rid of her!

353
00:22:52,552 --> 00:22:56,139
Touch her once more
or you will regret it.

354
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:01,186
Stop these shenanigangs, Saman-

355
00:23:02,259 --> 00:23:03,469
Zein Shion.

356
00:23:06,125 --> 00:23:07,125
Why should I?

357
00:23:07,376 --> 00:23:08,711
Aren't I right?

358
00:23:09,814 --> 00:23:10,815
First of all

359
00:23:11,266 --> 00:23:14,102
you don't have the right
to implement punishments

360
00:23:14,514 --> 00:23:16,391
because only Supremo can do that.

361
00:23:17,311 --> 00:23:18,354
Second

362
00:23:18,747 --> 00:23:20,373
the way you're standing here

363
00:23:21,885 --> 00:23:24,221
comes off as disrespectful.

364
00:23:25,073 --> 00:23:26,115
How do you expect

365
00:23:26,140 --> 00:23:27,891
to earn our respect?

366
00:23:30,243 --> 00:23:31,411
And lastly,

367
00:23:31,980 --> 00:23:34,817
I am the Supreme Student Secretary.

368
00:23:35,646 --> 00:23:38,024
I have the right to object

369
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,036
your decisions.

370
00:23:42,102 --> 00:23:44,896
Am I forgetting anything else,
Madam Violet?

371
00:23:45,958 --> 00:23:47,084
Supremo

372
00:23:47,471 --> 00:23:48,973
control your secretary.

373
00:24:00,286 --> 00:24:01,328
She's right though.

374
00:24:02,445 --> 00:24:03,696
Supremo

375
00:24:04,201 --> 00:24:07,537
you should punish this
rude secretary of yours.

376
00:24:07,804 --> 00:24:08,804
Why?

377
00:24:09,462 --> 00:24:10,462
She actually deserves an award

378
00:24:10,463 --> 00:24:11,673
rather than a punishment

379
00:24:12,507 --> 00:24:14,427
because from all the secretaries
I've worked with

380
00:24:15,135 --> 00:24:16,594
she's the only one who knows

381
00:24:16,595 --> 00:24:19,639
that I'm the only one who can
implement punishments here.

382
00:24:21,890 --> 00:24:23,851
Now, based on student council rules

383
00:24:25,632 --> 00:24:26,800
that seems impressive.

384
00:24:27,464 --> 00:24:29,174
Isn't it, Madam?

385
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:31,726
Ace Craige.

386
00:24:34,244 --> 00:24:35,912
Am I forgetting something.

387
00:24:36,241 --> 00:24:37,534
Sir Francisco?

388
00:24:39,326 --> 00:24:41,328
No but

389
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:44,623
let's not forget why we are here.

390
00:24:44,932 --> 00:24:47,810
Let's go back to what I
was saying a while ago

391
00:24:48,335 --> 00:24:50,878
let us talk about the big event

392
00:24:50,879 --> 00:24:53,840
that's going to happen in this school.

393
00:24:54,174 --> 00:24:58,053
It will last one whole week!

394
00:24:58,261 --> 00:25:00,263
And we will call it.

395
00:25:00,430 --> 00:25:02,348
Bloody Week.

396
00:25:02,349 --> 00:25:06,895
Where killing is legal in
a span of a week.

397
00:25:07,812 --> 00:25:09,439
At any time.

398
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:11,482
Good luck everybody.

399
00:25:11,804 --> 00:25:15,402
Seems like half of Hell
University's population

400
00:25:15,542 --> 00:25:16,796
will die.

401
00:25:17,773 --> 00:25:18,773
Seriously?

402
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:23,495
Do you have a problem with that.

403
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,202
Ms. Shion?

404
00:25:29,511 --> 00:25:31,346
If that's set in stone

405
00:25:32,711 --> 00:25:34,129
please excuse me

406
00:25:35,031 --> 00:25:36,908
I'll be preparing for Bloody Week.

407
00:25:40,489 --> 00:25:42,033
Seems like we all should.

408
00:25:57,320 --> 00:26:00,699
So, how are you feeling now, Vanessa?

409
00:26:01,957 --> 00:26:03,083
Scared

410
00:26:03,841 --> 00:26:05,009
but great.

411
00:26:07,773 --> 00:26:09,483
They deserved it.

412
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,667
That's not even half of my rage.

413
00:26:11,692 --> 00:26:13,361
You know what,
you're reckless too.

414
00:26:14,102 --> 00:26:15,478
Why did you do that?

415
00:26:16,381 --> 00:26:17,882
Do you want to end up like me?

416
00:26:18,176 --> 00:26:19,427
Marked by the admin?

417
00:26:19,816 --> 00:26:20,816
At least

418
00:26:20,985 --> 00:26:22,320
there's both of us.

419
00:26:22,618 --> 00:26:25,037
It'll be difficult to keep track.

420
00:26:27,605 --> 00:26:29,148
You're so brave.

421
00:26:29,818 --> 00:26:31,236
You're overreacting.

422
00:26:32,727 --> 00:26:33,728
I'm serious

423
00:26:34,641 --> 00:26:35,851
that's why.

424
00:26:36,561 --> 00:26:38,480
I'm falling in love with you harder.

425
00:26:39,515 --> 00:26:40,515
Excuse me.

426
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:42,893
You're close to getting hit.

427
00:26:44,326 --> 00:26:45,744
But wait guys.

428
00:26:46,418 --> 00:26:47,794
I almost died there.

429
00:26:48,832 --> 00:26:49,959
Good thing.

430
00:26:51,303 --> 00:26:53,805
Madam Secretary was to the rescue.

431
00:26:53,977 --> 00:26:55,979
Madam Violet couldn't
even do anything about it.

432
00:26:56,097 --> 00:26:57,223
Nothing?

433
00:26:58,773 --> 00:27:01,901
But Zein, what you did had me worried.

434
00:27:02,136 --> 00:27:03,930
How were you aware of those rules?

435
00:27:05,168 --> 00:27:06,377
Were those true or

436
00:27:06,871 --> 00:27:08,191
did you make them up last minute?

437
00:27:08,573 --> 00:27:10,867
Zein wouldn't lie about that.

438
00:27:11,128 --> 00:27:12,796
She'll be in more danger.

439
00:27:13,518 --> 00:27:14,645
Those rules were true.

440
00:27:15,447 --> 00:27:17,907
I read them in the SSG bylaws.

441
00:27:18,085 --> 00:27:19,669
Supremo is the only one

442
00:27:19,694 --> 00:27:21,339
who has the power to implement
death as a punishment

443
00:27:21,363 --> 00:27:24,449
to any one who breaks the law

444
00:27:25,017 --> 00:27:28,020
or whoever rebels against Hell University.

445
00:27:28,536 --> 00:27:31,414
Supremo trumps HU headmasters.

446
00:27:31,682 --> 00:27:32,682
Wise...

447
00:27:32,925 --> 00:27:35,720
at least we know that the student
council is pro students.

448
00:27:36,392 --> 00:27:37,519
I almost forgot

449
00:27:37,888 --> 00:27:40,266
our grades are taken care of.

450
00:27:40,719 --> 00:27:42,930
Sir Alvarez has our back.

451
00:27:48,056 --> 00:27:49,349
Hello?

452
00:27:49,782 --> 00:27:51,201
Did you hear what I just said?

453
00:27:51,335 --> 00:27:52,294
I said

454
00:27:52,319 --> 00:27:54,562
we're not failing history class.

455
00:27:55,031 --> 00:27:56,574
Shouldn't we celebrate?

456
00:27:58,349 --> 00:27:59,272
You know

457
00:27:59,438 --> 00:28:02,440
our questions aren't going
to answer themselves.

458
00:28:03,562 --> 00:28:05,439
Why did you keep that from us, Zein?

459
00:28:08,083 --> 00:28:09,751
What do you mean?

460
00:28:10,203 --> 00:28:13,186
It's like you don't want
to leave anymore.

461
00:28:14,450 --> 00:28:15,242
What?

462
00:28:15,267 --> 00:28:17,644
We know that you know HU's secrets.

463
00:28:17,825 --> 00:28:20,452
And we know that you can't
leave this place already.

464
00:28:21,304 --> 00:28:22,674
Wait, what?

465
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:25,110
How did you find out?

466
00:28:25,290 --> 00:28:26,916
Do you think we're noobs?

467
00:28:27,909 --> 00:28:30,704
Of course we notice it when you're
keeping something from us.

468
00:28:31,403 --> 00:28:32,988
You're our friend.

469
00:28:33,410 --> 00:28:34,828
You're so hard-headed.

470
00:28:35,039 --> 00:28:38,459
You always help us but you
don't think of yourself.

471
00:28:39,411 --> 00:28:41,288
I need to protect all of you.

472
00:28:42,033 --> 00:28:45,787
I will do everything in my power so
all of you can leave this hellhole.

473
00:28:46,223 --> 00:28:47,265
You mean us.

474
00:28:47,950 --> 00:28:50,286
All of us wil leave this hellhole.

475
00:28:50,597 --> 00:28:53,016
Do you think we'll let
you be stuck here?

476
00:28:54,022 --> 00:28:55,273
I'll put you guys first, Matt.

477
00:28:55,862 --> 00:28:57,196
I have to.

478
00:28:59,352 --> 00:29:01,146
We'll escape together, Zein.

479
00:29:01,438 --> 00:29:02,981
No one gets left behind, remember?

480
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:04,834
Right, we'll stick together.

481
00:29:06,081 --> 00:29:07,875
And don't worry

482
00:29:08,491 --> 00:29:10,053
we already know.

483
00:29:10,738 --> 00:29:11,906
What do you mean?

484
00:29:12,031 --> 00:29:13,533
We know about Dr. Quizon

485
00:29:13,780 --> 00:29:17,579
and the secret formula to bring
the dead back to life

486
00:29:17,843 --> 00:29:19,929
and I swear that's so cool.

487
00:29:20,404 --> 00:29:21,280
And to be honest

488
00:29:21,305 --> 00:29:22,847
I thought it was a joke.

489
00:29:24,787 --> 00:29:26,836
If we don't get out of here

490
00:29:27,681 --> 00:29:30,684
we'll rot together in this hellhole.

491
00:29:31,619 --> 00:29:33,079
You’re not alone, Zein.

492
00:29:33,745 --> 00:29:36,289
We won't ever leave you alone.

493
00:29:36,664 --> 00:29:38,708
We'll die here together.

494
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:47,196
No. I can't let us die here.

495
00:29:58,190 --> 00:29:59,817
You're heartless!

496
00:30:10,468 --> 00:30:12,929
You can do something about this.

497
00:30:14,953 --> 00:30:16,454
But you're afraid.

498
00:30:18,119 --> 00:30:19,495
That's where you're wrong.

499
00:30:20,324 --> 00:30:21,700
I can't do anything.

500
00:30:22,366 --> 00:30:24,159
I'm just a secretary.

501
00:30:25,765 --> 00:30:27,516
Why was she able to do something?

502
00:30:29,342 --> 00:30:30,843
I thought

503
00:30:31,659 --> 00:30:33,352
you're like Samantha.

504
00:30:34,458 --> 00:30:35,500
But I was wrong.

505
00:30:35,824 --> 00:30:36,908
You're a coward.

506
00:30:37,300 --> 00:30:38,968
Who is this Samantha
you're talking about?

507
00:30:39,852 --> 00:30:41,938
Why is everyone calling me that?

508
00:30:43,047 --> 00:30:44,381
Who is she?

509
00:30:45,149 --> 00:30:47,109
She was once a newbie

510
00:30:47,265 --> 00:30:48,349
like you.

511
00:30:50,899 --> 00:30:52,734
But the difference between the two of you

512
00:30:52,735 --> 00:30:59,161
(Watch on www.kissasia.club Support Admin)

513
00:30:53,186 --> 00:30:54,186
is that

514
00:30:54,755 --> 00:30:56,214
she helped us.

515
00:30:58,462 --> 00:31:00,756
Was she THE former SSG Secretary?

516
00:31:03,138 --> 00:31:05,015
I need your help!

517
00:31:06,101 --> 00:31:08,481
I don't know how long I'll survive

518
00:31:08,506 --> 00:31:11,050
from all the serums
they've injected in me.

519
00:31:17,957 --> 00:31:19,458
What happened to you?

520
00:31:22,035 --> 00:31:24,704
They used me as a human test subject.

521
00:31:25,916 --> 00:31:30,142
They experimented on me.

522
00:31:31,613 --> 00:31:34,866
I was one of their test subjects for
the serum that they're making.

523
00:31:36,451 --> 00:31:37,493
Serum?

524
00:31:39,035 --> 00:31:40,035
Wait

525
00:31:40,334 --> 00:31:42,044
did they take you to the laboratory?

526
00:31:43,214 --> 00:31:44,549
Do you know where it's hidden?

527
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,185
Don't stand in their way

528
00:31:47,378 --> 00:31:49,297
if you don't want to end up like me.

529
00:31:50,456 --> 00:31:52,125
How can I help you

530
00:31:52,465 --> 00:31:55,302
if you can't tell me where they took you?

531
00:31:56,391 --> 00:31:58,268
You don't know what you're dealing with.

532
00:31:58,973 --> 00:32:01,351
Just help me.

533
00:32:02,182 --> 00:32:04,184
But how can I help you

534
00:32:05,219 --> 00:32:08,430
if you won't show me where
the secret lab is?

535
00:32:10,747 --> 00:32:13,000
Can you help me or not?

536
00:32:14,391 --> 00:32:15,391
Us?

537
00:32:16,449 --> 00:32:17,492
There are others?

538
00:32:20,578 --> 00:32:22,746
Wait, where are you going?

539
00:32:22,747 --> 00:32:24,247
I still need answers!

540
00:32:24,248 --> 00:32:25,625
Where is the laboratory?

541
00:32:27,889 --> 00:32:29,641
Didn't I already warn you?

542
00:32:37,910 --> 00:32:39,912
Stay away from Alvarez.

543
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:43,055
Why do you care?

544
00:32:44,168 --> 00:32:45,920
So stupid.

545
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:11,364
So slow, huh?

546
00:33:15,758 --> 00:33:16,758
You know

547
00:33:17,759 --> 00:33:19,177
you did a great job at the party.

548
00:33:21,816 --> 00:33:24,930
Just don't ever cross the admin again.

549
00:33:25,906 --> 00:33:26,906
Or me.

550
00:33:30,138 --> 00:33:31,138
Hey

551
00:33:31,690 --> 00:33:33,247
what's bothering you?

552
00:33:37,737 --> 00:33:38,737
Hey...

553
00:33:39,544 --> 00:33:40,795
what's wrong with you?

554
00:33:41,741 --> 00:33:43,243
I don't have a problem.

555
00:33:45,231 --> 00:33:46,231
Look.

556
00:33:46,801 --> 00:33:47,969
I'm just tired.

557
00:33:48,666 --> 00:33:51,765
Can you please leave me alone?

558
00:33:52,779 --> 00:33:54,572
So I can be done with this

559
00:33:54,974 --> 00:33:55,974
and get some rest.

560
00:34:00,474 --> 00:34:01,474
Let me help you.

561
00:34:01,679 --> 00:34:02,657
Let me get that.

562
00:34:02,682 --> 00:34:03,682
You don't have to.

563
00:34:04,415 --> 00:34:05,415
I can handle this.

564
00:34:05,756 --> 00:34:06,924
This is my punishment right?

565
00:34:07,825 --> 00:34:08,993
I can do it by my own.

566
00:34:34,225 --> 00:34:36,102
I'll get a rag.

567
00:34:42,290 --> 00:34:44,672
Can this day get any weirder?

568
00:34:44,697 --> 00:34:46,282
What is he planning?

569
00:34:46,626 --> 00:34:50,964
Why is he helping me when it's
him who gave me this punishment?

570
00:35:12,621 --> 00:35:15,082
Have you found a rag?

571
00:35:15,604 --> 00:35:16,604
Yes.

572
00:35:22,242 --> 00:35:23,577
Don't touch anything

573
00:35:24,913 --> 00:35:27,332
or else they'll say I don't respect you.

574
00:35:29,227 --> 00:35:31,369
Do you really believe or care
about the opinions of others?

575
00:35:31,573 --> 00:35:32,866
I don't want to get in trouble.

576
00:35:33,653 --> 00:35:35,071
You won't get in trouble.

577
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:37,636
Just don’t be reckless again.

578
00:35:40,820 --> 00:35:41,820
Ms. Shion.

579
00:35:51,390 --> 00:35:52,432
Are you being serious?

580
00:35:53,845 --> 00:35:55,055
Do I look like I'm joking?

581
00:35:56,731 --> 00:35:58,941
This is an order from the SSG President

582
00:36:00,628 --> 00:36:01,628
if I say something

583
00:36:02,710 --> 00:36:03,710
you answer quickly.

584
00:36:04,946 --> 00:36:05,946
Got it?

585
00:36:08,326 --> 00:36:09,326
Hey

586
00:36:09,833 --> 00:36:10,833
answer me.

587
00:36:12,472 --> 00:36:13,472
Yes.

588
00:36:23,606 --> 00:36:24,606
You know

589
00:36:26,037 --> 00:36:27,938
you just might be my Achilles' heel.

590
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,040
Ms. Shion.

591
00:36:55,978 --> 00:36:56,978
Here...

592
00:36:58,188 --> 00:36:59,188
for you.

593
00:37:00,398 --> 00:37:01,398
What's that?

594
00:37:04,434 --> 00:37:05,434
A gift.

595
00:37:24,191 --> 00:37:25,275
You're being quiet again.

596
00:37:26,798 --> 00:37:28,508
I already accepted your gift.

597
00:37:29,495 --> 00:37:30,968
What else do you want me to say?

598
00:37:32,087 --> 00:37:33,247
Aren't you going to thank me?

599
00:37:38,395 --> 00:37:39,395
Thank you.

600
00:37:43,655 --> 00:37:44,739
I'll head out.

601
00:37:47,780 --> 00:37:50,535
You should go back to the SSG too

602
00:37:52,112 --> 00:37:53,871
before Bloody Night.

603
00:37:55,613 --> 00:37:59,090
Does that mean that you care about me?

604
00:38:04,465 --> 00:38:05,465
No it doesn't.

605
00:38:05,917 --> 00:38:07,210
You wish.

606
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:08,494
Just so you know.

607
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:09,394
FYI

608
00:38:09,610 --> 00:38:11,445
I wouldn't care even

609
00:38:11,470 --> 00:38:12,595
if you got stuck outside
during Bloody Night.

610
00:38:12,596 --> 00:38:13,840
Or even if you die.

611
00:38:15,684 --> 00:38:16,863
You don't have to worry.

612
00:38:20,244 --> 00:38:21,284
I can take care of myself.

613
00:38:22,090 --> 00:38:23,090
Ms. Shion.

614
00:38:24,362 --> 00:38:25,362
Be careful.

615
00:38:28,950 --> 00:38:30,910
Okay. Bye, Supremo.

616
00:38:31,699 --> 00:38:32,699
Sleep well.

617
00:38:33,576 --> 00:38:34,936
I still have more to do for you...

618
00:38:35,902 --> 00:38:36,902
Zein.

619
00:38:37,910 --> 00:38:41,043
Huh? He called me by my first name.

620
00:39:00,445 --> 00:39:01,445
I'm so hungry.

621
00:39:04,369 --> 00:39:05,287
Look who's here.

622
00:39:05,374 --> 00:39:06,551
Hi, Zein.

623
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:09,817
What's up?

624
00:39:10,599 --> 00:39:12,643
Good thing you're here before the alarm.

625
00:39:12,863 --> 00:39:13,740
Thank you, brother.

626
00:39:13,741 --> 00:39:14,492
Let's eat first

627
00:39:14,493 --> 00:39:15,867
before the official start

628
00:39:15,868 --> 00:39:16,868
of Bloody Week.

629
00:39:17,620 --> 00:39:18,471
What is this?

630
00:39:18,679 --> 00:39:19,680
Our last meal on earth?

631
00:39:19,853 --> 00:39:21,682
Hey, don't be like that.

632
00:39:21,707 --> 00:39:25,835
Can't we just eat something
delicious peacefully

633
00:39:25,836 --> 00:39:28,090
before the riot outside starts?

634
00:39:28,551 --> 00:39:29,715
Let's enjoy the food.

635
00:39:29,716 --> 00:39:31,108
Matt cooked it.

636
00:39:31,359 --> 00:39:33,153
Wow, you cooked again?

637
00:39:33,713 --> 00:39:35,005
This should be delicious!

638
00:39:35,030 --> 00:39:37,551
To lure you back early in the dorm.

639
00:39:38,682 --> 00:39:39,682
By the way

640
00:39:39,951 --> 00:39:40,951
how's your punishment?

641
00:39:41,186 --> 00:39:42,785
It seems like you finished early today.

642
00:39:43,507 --> 00:39:45,067
It's because someone helped me.

643
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:47,080
Who?

644
00:39:49,044 --> 00:39:50,086
Supremo.

645
00:39:50,738 --> 00:39:51,861
Wow, Zein.

646
00:39:51,862 --> 00:39:53,029
You're built different now

647
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:56,488
even the student government
president is helping you clean.

648
00:39:56,951 --> 00:39:57,647
Hey

649
00:39:57,672 --> 00:39:59,106
I didn’t command him to help me.

650
00:40:00,312 --> 00:40:01,312
He did it willingly.

651
00:40:02,057 --> 00:40:03,308
Why are you being defensive?

652
00:40:03,996 --> 00:40:07,419
Maybe you're crushing on Supremo?

653
00:40:08,977 --> 00:40:11,188
Watch your words, Van.

654
00:40:11,981 --> 00:40:13,781
We're not even friends,
how can we be lovers?

655
00:40:15,285 --> 00:40:16,328
Whatever.

656
00:40:17,523 --> 00:40:19,567
Matt's dish seems delicious!

657
00:40:20,002 --> 00:40:21,211
Adobo!

658
00:40:21,899 --> 00:40:23,609
Let's eat guys.

659
00:40:24,057 --> 00:40:26,601
Yeah, while the rice is still warm.

660
00:40:47,874 --> 00:40:49,083
Stay away from Ace.

661
00:40:52,173 --> 00:40:53,173
Huh?

662
00:40:53,883 --> 00:40:54,883
Why?

663
00:40:56,802 --> 00:40:57,949
I'll get water.

664
00:41:05,948 --> 00:41:07,116
Did I say something wrong?

665
00:41:08,195 --> 00:41:09,405
He's just jealous.

666
00:41:09,754 --> 00:41:11,846
You know he's in love with you.

667
00:41:11,871 --> 00:41:13,551
You should take it easy.

668
00:41:13,967 --> 00:41:14,967
He's right, Zein.

669
00:41:14,996 --> 00:41:16,665
Don't be a griefer towards Matt.

670
00:41:16,934 --> 00:41:18,811
He's just worried about you.

671
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:20,360
Griefer? What?

672
00:41:21,218 --> 00:41:22,219
Just look it up.

673
00:41:22,509 --> 00:41:23,509
Come on, let's eat.

674
00:41:24,128 --> 00:41:25,128
Go ahead.

675
00:41:34,871 --> 00:41:35,871
Are you okay?

676
00:41:36,169 --> 00:41:37,170
Water, you want some?

677
00:41:45,392 --> 00:41:47,403
I have weapons ready for us.

678
00:41:54,108 --> 00:41:55,401
What weapons?

679
00:42:26,550 --> 00:42:27,593
What's this for?

680
00:42:28,143 --> 00:42:29,559
We need to be ready.

681
00:42:31,167 --> 00:42:32,376
For Bloody Night?

682
00:42:33,372 --> 00:42:34,373
Week, Zein.

683
00:42:34,735 --> 00:42:35,735
Bloody Week.

684
00:42:39,504 --> 00:42:42,132
I'm not sure if I'm ready for this.

685
00:42:42,403 --> 00:42:44,613
Didn't we talk about this already, Van?

686
00:42:45,868 --> 00:42:48,246
And this is for emergency purposes only.

687
00:42:49,013 --> 00:42:50,293
Let's just hide them in our bags

688
00:42:50,428 --> 00:42:51,428
for protection.

689
00:42:51,792 --> 00:42:52,792
Right, Matt?

690
00:42:53,389 --> 00:42:55,057
This is a bad idea, guys.

691
00:43:01,267 --> 00:43:02,601
This is necessary.

692
00:43:04,209 --> 00:43:07,173
Starting tonight until the end of the week

693
00:43:07,550 --> 00:43:08,931
we’ll walk along side death.

694
00:43:09,599 --> 00:43:11,595
So if you don't want to go with him

695
00:43:12,475 --> 00:43:13,727
we need to defend ourselves.

696
00:43:14,066 --> 00:43:15,066
No!

697
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:17,182
I don't want this, Dave!

698
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:19,978
We're not murderers.

699
00:43:20,612 --> 00:43:23,699
We're just defending ourselves, okay?

700
00:43:26,490 --> 00:43:28,408
We need to survive Bloody Week

701
00:43:29,066 --> 00:43:30,876
if we want to leave this place.

702
00:43:33,228 --> 00:43:34,228
Mia...

703
00:43:34,877 --> 00:43:37,204
Our lives are in danger, Zein.

704
00:43:37,926 --> 00:43:40,136
If we're not going to help ourselves

705
00:43:40,532 --> 00:43:42,075
who's going to help us?

706
00:43:42,691 --> 00:43:43,691
No one!

707
00:43:50,548 --> 00:43:52,079
I'm going to hide these two, Zein.

708
00:43:52,104 --> 00:43:54,064
Just in case you change your mind.

709
00:43:55,675 --> 00:43:56,676
Matt...

710
00:44:18,128 --> 00:44:19,420
Get her!

711
00:44:19,421 --> 00:44:21,896
Why are you doing this?

712
00:44:21,921 --> 00:44:23,589
Why? You stole him from me!

713
00:44:35,397 --> 00:44:36,397
Zein!

714
00:44:36,563 --> 00:44:37,563
Zein!

715
00:44:41,224 --> 00:44:43,629
We can't do anything to save them.

716
00:44:44,004 --> 00:44:46,298
You might get hurt!

717
00:44:46,323 --> 00:44:48,116
Matt, if I can't do anything about this

718
00:44:48,117 --> 00:44:49,576
they'll kill each other.

719
00:44:50,536 --> 00:44:52,578
What's the point of Bloody Week

720
00:44:52,579 --> 00:44:53,893
if no one will die?

721
00:44:54,289 --> 00:44:56,127
Zein, we can't do anything about this.

722
00:44:56,667 --> 00:44:57,471
What?

723
00:44:57,496 --> 00:44:59,768
Fuck all of this! Someone stop them!

724
00:45:00,370 --> 00:45:02,776
We can't save everyone, Zein.

725
00:45:03,524 --> 00:45:06,610
We have bigger problems than this.

726
00:45:06,777 --> 00:45:07,579
She's right, Zein.

727
00:45:07,604 --> 00:45:09,127
Be strong, please!

728
00:45:09,304 --> 00:45:10,638
Listen to her, Zein!

729
00:45:10,639 --> 00:45:12,282
This isn't even the beginning.

730
00:45:12,626 --> 00:45:13,919
This is just the pre-game.

731
00:45:14,226 --> 00:45:16,060
I can't handle seeing
people kill each other

732
00:45:16,061 --> 00:45:17,538
without doing anything!

733
00:45:17,563 --> 00:45:17,898
Zein...

734
00:45:17,923 --> 00:45:19,763
What do you think you
can do about this, Zein?

735
00:45:20,077 --> 00:45:21,537
Huh? Tell us.

736
00:45:25,551 --> 00:45:26,551
Zein.

737
00:45:28,722 --> 00:45:29,722
Don't go near them.

738
00:47:41,377 --> 00:47:42,920
Die already!

739
00:48:18,348 --> 00:48:21,310
Just tell me where the
laboratory is hidden.

740
00:48:21,873 --> 00:48:23,124
I'll show it to you.

741
00:48:26,941 --> 00:48:28,485
We can't save everyone...

742
00:48:28,837 --> 00:48:29,837
Ms. Shion.

743
00:48:30,359 --> 00:48:32,111
Matt said the same thing.

744
00:48:38,651 --> 00:48:40,069
You know, Zein.

745
00:48:44,268 --> 00:48:46,078
From all that's been happening

746
00:48:46,104 --> 00:48:52,027
it eases my heart and mind
knowing we're all together.

747
00:48:53,570 --> 00:48:54,696
Happy birthday, Zein.

748
00:49:01,456 --> 00:49:02,957
That's our boy!

749
00:49:10,045 --> 00:49:11,045
Hey

750
00:49:13,548 --> 00:49:14,883
why are you so damn happy?

751
00:49:16,786 --> 00:49:18,162
It's none of your business.

752
00:49:25,221 --> 00:49:26,723
Why are you so happy?

753
00:49:28,146 --> 00:49:29,146
Supremo.

754
00:49:32,052 --> 00:49:33,637
I secured the files.

755
00:49:35,213 --> 00:49:36,297
You can go now.

756
00:49:37,531 --> 00:49:39,032
Matthew might be looking for you.

757
00:49:41,661 --> 00:49:42,661
Obviously.
